ce:section.ce:para:
To investigate the protective and therapeutic effects of FDCDs on PD, FDCDs were synthesized via a one-step hydrothermal method (Fig. 1
                     ), followed by the detection of their morphology, zeta potential, photophysical properties, SO4
                     2− concentration, and surface chemistry. Subsequently, the antagonistic effect of FDCDs against 1-Methyl-4-phenylpyridinium ion (MPP+) and H2O2-induced cellular damage was evaluated through cytocompatibility analysis, anti-apoptosis assay, and detection of mitochondrial membrane potential in vitro. After the verification of the ability of FDCDs to cross the BBB using near-infrared fluorescence imaging, a PD mouse model was induced using MPTP, followed by administration of FDCDs through tail vein injection. Their motor behaviors were observed, and changes in body weight, tissue, and blood were analyzed, thus providing a proof-of-concept evaluation for the therapeutic efficacy of FDCDs in PD (Fig. 1).
